 Centane - The Centane Regional Magistrate’s Court convicted and sentenced a 27-year-old man, Asekho Kilani, to undergo 16 years imprisonment for rape. "The accused person was sentenced on Thursday last week at the Centane Regional Magistrate’s Court," said police spokesperson, Captain Jackson Manatha. "It is alleged that the accused accompanied a 23-year-old woman, who want to go to her boyfriend on the 21 June 2018, at about 21h30, at Rwantsana Locality, Qombolo Village, Centane. "While the two were on their way to the homestead of the victim’s boyfriend, the accused became vicious and threatened the victim with knife." He allegedly raped the victim. "A case of rape was registered at Centane Police Station. The accused was later traced, arrested and charged with rape." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 